<br>
 <p><img src="http://leagueofhonour.com/kyrialsignature.jpg">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=syllestraefv>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderating inconsistently<br>since Jun 2002</span><br>  Posts: 2192<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 5:29:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pets and weapons...</span><hr size=1> Generally speaking, weapons with procs.<br>
<br>
You can't reduce a pet's attack delay with a low delay weapon.<br>
<br>
You can increase their damage with a high damage weapon, but I'm uncertain if their delay also gets increased to match (ie: giving a level 1 skeleton a rusty halberd will let them hit for 20 damage, but I'm not sure if their attack delay goes up to 50).<br>
<br>
I find stuff like gnoll lariats (procs a stun) to be great weapons to give a pet.  Velium weapons are also cheap and will increase their damage output a tiny bit with the proc.<br>
<br>
- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhatha>Rhatha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Animist of Shar Vahl<br>The Dark Side wants YOU!</span><br>  Posts: 723<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/11/02 9:31:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://darklance.freewebspace.com/images/rhatha.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pets and weapons...</span><hr size=1> What she said.<br>
<br>
Also, I don't know if it matters for mage or chanter pets, but beastlord pets are coded as beastlords, so giving them weapons other than hand to hand can decrease their damage output due to lower skill caps.  I think mage/necro/chanter pets are coded as warriors, thus giving them hand to hand would be a very bad idea :P but I am not entirely sure on this.  Mebbe ask a mage who can summon fists of Ixiblat and parse them out. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=112438">Rhatha Sha`Naya</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> and Swiftclaw<br>
