Eating bunnies for 62 seasons!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braellarth>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 365<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/12/02 12:23:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=116.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: pets and weapons...</span><hr size=1> Halberds on pet's are just scary. I remember i loved to give them to my shadowknight pet because he could hit harder than me with them.<br>
<br>
Pets dont use slow delays, and pets will always use the wepon with the fastest delay you give them.<br>
<br>
Pets can wield a 2h &amp; 1h wepon if the 2h has a lower delay than the 1h. Example : goto chardok get a backpack of shovels and give your pet a sword + shovel, he will wield the shovel in one hand and sword in other. The delay doesnt make a difference on the pet's swings.<br>
<br>
Wepons from Kael are good, theres a really high damage one handed and bad delay - that is awsome for pets.<br>
<br>
There is also some wepons in PoM - Blam stick that will really improve your pet.<br>
<br>
Pets cant wield some 2h wepons also - Weighted axe will not work, and some other 2h wepons, i dont know why... they just dont, maybe pets cant wield 'lore' items i dont know,  but my pet wont wield a goranga club either....<br>
<br>
